   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lifeline out of poverty for Children in Zambia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Over half a million Zambian children are unable to access conventional education. Schools of Good Hope project works with Zambia&apos;s poorest communities, who have set up their own makeshift schools and enables them to provide the good standard of education they desire for their children. By training the untrained volunteer teachers and providing essential resources we can help give Zambia&apos;s poorest children a lifeline out of poverty.</narrative>
  </description>
